Quick Windows tip to keep me sane:

For Windows XP, install TweakUI from Microsoft, and turn on X11-like focus-follows-mouse mode.

[![TWEAKUI MOUSE](http://ootput.files.wordpress.com/2014/11/tweakui-mouse.jpg)](http://ootput.files.wordpress.com/2014/11/tweakui-mouse.jpg)

Install [KatMouse](http://ehiti.de/katmouse/) to allow mouse-wheel-scrolling for unfocused windows. This means that I don't need to focus a window by clicking on it in order to scroll its contents.
